CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1776795065
OL,3,CReform UK closes gap on Plaid Cymru in
OL,4,Crace to become Senedd's largest party
OL,6,FAccording to MRP modelling by YouGov
OL,7,Ffor ITV Wales in partnership with
OL,8,FCardiff University, under the new
OL,9,FD'Hondt voting system, this round of
OL,10,Fresults means Reform would win 37
OL,11,Fseats and Plaid Cymru would win 36.
OL,13,FWith both short of a majority it
OL,14,Fsparks more questions about potential
OL,15,Fdeals with other parties after Wales
OL,16,Fgoes to the polls in just over two
OL,17,Fweeks time.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1776795065
OL,3,CReform UK closes gap on Plaid Cymru in
OL,4,Crace to become Senedd's largest party
OL,6,FDr Jac Larner, from Cardiff
OL,7,FUniversity's Welsh Governance Centre
OL,8,Fsaid: "This poll shows another small
OL,9,Fdrop in support for Plaid Cymru,
OL,10,Fputting them level with Reform UK at
OL,11,F29%; YouGov's lowest Plaid estimate
OL,12,Fsince November 2024. All polls come
OL,13,Fwith a margin of error, and we should
OL,14,Fbe cautious about reading too much
OL,15,Finto a single result.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1776795065
OL,3,CReform UK closes gap on Plaid Cymru in
OL,4,Crace to become Senedd's largest party
OL,6,F"But taken alongside the broader
OL,7,Fpolling trend, the signal is clear:
OL,8,Fthe race for the largest party remains
OL,9,Fbetween Plaid Cymru and Reform UK,
OL,10,Fwith every other party - including
OL,11,FLabour, who were dominant in Welsh
OL,12,Fpolitics not two years ago ` competing
OL,13,Ffor a distant third place and below.
OL,15,F"What that framing obscures, however,
OL,16,Fis that finishing first may matter
OL,17,Fless than it appears. Whichever party
OL,18,Fleads on seats will face the same
OL,19,Fcoalition arithmetic, and that
OL,20,Farithmetic is far more favourable to
OL,21,FPlaid than to Reform.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1776795065
OL,3,CReform UK closes gap on Plaid Cymru in
OL,4,Crace to become Senedd's largest party
OL,6,F"Plaid has credible partners in Labour
OL,7,Fand the Greens; a combination of those
OL,8,Fparties can reach a working majority.
OL,9,FReform has no such options.
OL,11,F"The only party that has indicated any
OL,12,Fwillingness to work with them is the
OL,13,FConservatives, who on these numbers
OL,14,Fwill not come close to bridging the
OL,15,Fgap to a Senedd majority. In a
OL,16,Fproportional system, the route to
OL,17,Fgovernment matters as much as the vote
OL,18,Fshare, and on that measure, the two
OL,19,Fparties are not as evenly matched as
OL,20,Fthe headline figures suggest.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1776795065
OL,3,CReform UK closes gap on Plaid Cymru in
OL,4,Crace to become Senedd's largest party
OL,6,F"A situation where Reform UK are the
OL,7,Flargest party but find themselves in
OL,8,Fopposition will nonetheless be a novel
OL,9,Fone for Welsh voters still adjusting
OL,10,Fto the realities of proportional
OL,11,Fgovernment formation."
OL,13,FThe poll keeps Labour on third place
OL,14,Fat 13% - netting approximately 12
OL,15,Fseats - but Welsh leader Eluned Morgan
OL,16,Fis still predicted to lose her seat.
OL,18,FThe Green Party has seen a modest
OL,19,Freduction in its share to 10% which
OL,20,Fwould translate to seven seats.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/10
